 AttachWCCheck msg;‚éïIO;DESIGN;TOL;par;box;id;fid;bpos;bsize;attach;eg;eposn;esize;aposn;asize;ok;pass;n;allfixed;atxt
‚çù Read every box's LIVE Posn/Size (‚éïWG) and compare to the Attach-correct
‚çù geometry for the CURRENT form size ‚Äî so it validates ANY resize (drag or the
‚çù ‚éïWS "Grow" button). Prints a PASS/FAIL table to the session. Works as the
‚çù Check-button callback AND is directly callable: AttachWCCheck 0
‚çù NOTE (Coord 'Pixel'): the docs say an ATTACHED edge's Posn/Size "remains
‚çù unaffected" by a resize. So the 'act' column shows exactly what ‚éïWG reports ‚Äî
‚çù compare it to 'exp' (the on-screen-correct geometry) to see what native does.
 ‚éïIO‚Üê1
 DESIGN‚Üê520 840 ‚ãÑ TOL‚Üê2
 par‚Üê'F1'‚éïWG'Size'
 ‚éï‚Üê''
 ‚éï‚Üê'Form size ',(‚çïpar),'   (baseline ',(‚çïDESIGN),')   tol=',‚çïTOL
 pass‚Üê0 ‚ãÑ n‚Üê0 ‚ãÑ allfixed‚Üê1
 :For box :In AttachWCBoxes
     (id bpos bsize attach)‚Üêbox
     fid‚Üê'F1.',id
     eg‚Üê(DESIGN par)AttachWCExpect(bpos bsize attach)
     (eposn esize)‚Üêeg
     aposn‚Üêfid ‚éïWG'Posn'
     asize‚Üêfid ‚éïWG'Size'
     ok‚Üê(TOL‚â•‚åà/|eposn-aposn)‚àßTOL‚â•‚åà/|esize-asize
     allfixed‚Üêallfixed‚àß(aposn‚â°bpos)‚àßasize‚â°bsize
     pass+‚Üêok ‚ãÑ n+‚Üê1
     atxt‚Üê¬Ø1‚Üì‚àäattach,¬®‚äÇ' '
     ‚éï‚Üê((1+ok)‚äÉ'FAIL' 'pass'),' ',(3‚Üëid),'  ',(26‚Üëatxt),'  exp ',(19‚Üë‚çïeposn,esize),'  act ',(19‚Üë‚çïaposn,asize)
 :EndFor
 ‚éï‚Üê(‚çïpass),'/',(‚çïn),' boxes match the Attach-correct geometry'
 :If allfixed‚àß~DESIGN‚â°par
     ‚éï‚Üê'>> Children unchanged though the form grew: this resize did NOT reconfigure'
     ‚éï‚Üê'>> them. If you clicked Grow (‚éïWS Size), DRAG the form edge instead ‚Äî Attach'
     ‚éï‚Üê'>> may respond only to a USER resize, not to altering the Size property.'
 :EndIf
